  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Shamrica Alberta-Lynette Keys not in court, in custody.  Attorney Brett Lee Copeland appeared by video for Shamrica Alberta-Lynette Keys.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Case called at Court's request.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Court vacates previous sentencing.  For reasons stated on the record, Court orders 175 days in the House of Correction, 175 days time served.  THIS IS A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  

All other conditions of sentencing to remain.

Defendant Shamrica Alberta-Lynette Keys in court, in custody.  Attorney Brett Lee Copeland in court for Shamrica Alberta-Lynette Keys.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Plea and sentencing hearing held. State has filed an AMENDED information. Defense counsel acknowledges receipt, waives reading, and enters a temporary not guilty plea. Parties have reached an agreement. State places offer on the record. Defense and defendant are in agreement.

AS TO AMENDED COUNTS 1, 2, AND 3: Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Parties prepared to proceed with sentencing. State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law. Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing. Additional statement made by Mario R.

AS TO COUNT 1: Court sentenced the defendant to serve 12 MONTHS in the House of Correction.
Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 24 MONTHS.

AS TO COUNT 2: Court sentenced the defendant to serve 6 MONTHS in the House of Correction, with credit for 6 MONTHS time served. A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

AS TO COUNT 3: Court sentenced the defendant to 24 MONTHS PROBATION. Court WITHHELD sentence.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- Complete Parenting Classes.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety.
- Mental health evaluation; take all prescribed medications.
- No contact with victim.
- No contact with firearms.
- Provide a DNA sample.
- DV assessments imposed, as to all counts.
- Defendant to pay all non-waivable costs, assessments and surcharges, including the DNA and DV surcharges during the period of probation. Failure to pay the costs and surcharges will result in a civil judgment. Court WAIVED all other court costs, fees, and surcharges due to inability to pay.

*Court advised defendant of appellant rights. 
*Court advised defendant due to this DV conviction he may never possess firearms or ammunition.
